"Data is without doubt the ‘new oil’ – the currency that now underpins the digital economy. But in the wake of the Cambridge Analytica and Facebook misuse scandal, the concept of data monetisation is rightly under serious scrutiny. As we enter a new era of data privacy, from the recently implemented EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) to rapidly growing awareness of the way personal data is harvested and mined, organisations can no longer adopt a cavalier attitude to customer data."
